<p><strong>ibrandIQ as Tecnical Director</strong> <em>July 2018 ~ July 2019</em></p>

<p>Working at ibrandIQ, I was brought in to maintain their existing where-to-buy platform. This quickly moved to into developing the next version of the platform.</p>

<p>The new platform organised products from a global catalogue of retailers, in multiple languages. It also took a different approach to the where-to-buy solution which made it far more flexible than the previous system. The outcome meant there were less daily admin tasks, which allowed the team to work on other more critical projects.</p>

<p><strong>Bud. as UI Developer</strong> <em>July 2017 ~ Feb 2018</em></p>

<p>I joined Bud to head up their front-end team, and move the web app forward. I worked closely with the in-house design team; the goal was to design and develop a functional and user-friendly platform which would enable users to aggregate all their financial data.</p>

<p><strong>Capital on Tap as Senior UI Developer</strong> <em>February 2017 ~ July 2017</em></p>

<p>I was asked to return to Capital on Tap as they needed someone to create a living style guide and develop guidelines for their front end projects. While there I worked on some public facing pages to help promote the company and build there online presence.</p>

<p><strong>Capital on Tap as Developer</strong> <em>April 2015 ~ April 2016</em></p>

<p>I primarily worked on front-end projects optimising, reworking and improving load times to the public facing sites. I also led the creation and implementation of a custom SASS library into existing web solutions projects and training members of the team on how to use the library.</p>

<p>During my time at Capital on Tap, I also had exposure to some of the .NET back end. Including working on unit tests, developing the customer portals so users could manage their accounts online.</p>

<p><strong>Balmoral Financial as Senior Developer</strong> <em>November 2014 ~ March 2015</em></p>

