<p>I designed and developed the UI concept for the user and admin areas which were built using .NET MVC, and WebAPI. Along with the admin areas, I also created a conceptual native Android application. This app used Bluetooth LE to communicate with prototype devices and transferred data to the prototype.</p>

<p><strong>NASDAQ as Senior Designer/Developer</strong> <em>October 2012 ~ March 2014</em></p>

<p>During my time at NASDAQ, I was the only designer/developer on the team. Utilising the in-house framework, I developed newsroom sites for various big brand clients such as Facebook, Sony, Gatwick, Mattel and Centre Parcs.</p>

<p>I also designed responsive, eye-catching designs for clients including Sony, and Gatwick. Two of which were put forward for ‚Äòdesign impact‚Äô awards.</p>

<p>Also, while working at NASDAQ, I became a Microsoft Certified Professional.</p>

<p><strong>The Whisky Exchange as Front-end developer</strong> <em>May 2012 ~ October 2012</em></p>

